<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99867319381840></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99867319381840><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=7&mid=99867319381840>RE: Don't Nuke in Groups</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Aug 24th 1:13 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>i think there are times when a cleric can occasionally nuke.  i have a L59 cleric on e'ci and i have been grouping in sebilis for quite some time. is seb, there is always an enchanter in the group and most of the time that enc is L54+ (which means clarity 2).  if the group has 1 or 2 high level warriors, the need to heal them is minimal.  if i am at full mana, the group is buffed, and no one needs a heal, then i throw in a round of nuke, stun, nuke.  it brings me down to 80% mana, but it is an extra 1570 damage on the mob and then i have a reason to med.  i would never blatently nuke a mob until i am out of mana, that would just be foolish, but if you have a good group that rarely needs heals, then it is warrented to throw in a nuke here and there.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
