<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99833305794674></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99833305794674><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=7&mid=99833305794674>RE: Don't Nuke in Groups</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=43868><span id= >Stiffee</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>4 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Aug 20th 2:44 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The other night I had a warrior blame my cleric (lev 29 at the time) for "letting him die."  He neglected to mention that he had just pulled three giants down on us in FM when I had just said I was OOM.<br><br>How many times does this happen in groups then the cleric gets blamed?  I am sick and tired of getting blamed when someone does something STOOPID and dies.<br><br>If you are a tank reading this remember that the cleric can only heal you if you give thema chance to regen mana.  And if you pull a multi you darn well better be ready to get the MOBs off of the cleric after he/she heals you.  If a multi gets pulled by my group I try everything I can to heal after at least the first one has been killed.  If the tank is about to die then I DO heal them- then as usual have to shout for help cause I am getting bashed and can't cast.<br><br>I guess my point boils down to this: Pullers that don't pay any attention to healer's mana- especially when the healer says Lom or OOM are taking their lives into their own hands.<br><br>Additionally- with regards to the original topic in this thread, the only time I ever dd is when I am FM and need to use some mana.  Being FM with nothing to do with it is like having a full can of coffee with no can opener- it isn't doing you any good till you get it out of the can.<br><br>Heelyougood Rezformoney<br>Cleric of 31 seasons, Morrell-Thule<br>Protectors of the Unknown<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
